{"parse":{"title":"The Francis Bacon Opera","pageid":38501600,"revid":832469952,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><i><b>The Francis Bacon Opera</b></i> is a comic <a href=\"/wiki/Chamber_opera\" title=\"Chamber opera\">chamber opera</a> in one act composed by <a href=\"/wiki/Stephen_Crowe_(composer)\" title=\"Stephen Crowe (composer)\">Stephen Crowe</a>. The <a href=\"/wiki/Libretto\" title=\"Libretto\">libretto</a> is based on Crowe's transcript of <a href=\"/wiki/Melvyn_Bragg\" title=\"Melvyn Bragg\">Melvyn Bragg</a>'s interview with the British artist <a href=\"/wiki/Francis_Bacon_(artist)\" title=\"Francis Bacon (artist)\">Francis Bacon</a>, filmed for <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_South_Bank_Show\" title=\"The South Bank Show\">The South Bank Show</a></i> in 1985. The opera was first performed in its final version on 8 August 2012 in London, and went on to win the Hilton Edwards Award in May 2013.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Background_and_performance_history\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Background and performance history</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Roles_and_premiere_cast\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Roles and premiere cast</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Critical_reception\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Critical reception</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Background_and_performance_history\">Background and performance history</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Francis_Bacon_Opera&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Background and performance history\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The opera is scored for two solo singers (<a href=\"/wiki/Tenor\" title=\"Tenor\">tenors</a>) and a piano, and has a running time of 55 minutes. The libretto is derived from three portions of a documentary devoted to Francis Bacon which was filmed in 1985 for <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_South_Bank_Show\" title=\"The South Bank Show\">The South Bank Show</a></i>. In the episode, Melvin Bragg interviewed Bacon over a lengthy wine-fuelled lunch in a London restaurant. Bragg later recalled:\n</p>\n<blockquote><p>When Francis Bacon and myself appeared on the <i>Southbank Show</i> and for a few minutes were caught in a state of naked inebriation, it provided I think, an insight into Francis as a man and as a painter. So I left it in the film.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></blockquote>\n<p><i>The Francis Bacon Opera</i> was performed as \"a work in progress\" at the <a href=\"/wiki/Grimeborn\" title=\"Grimeborn\">Grimeborn Opera Festival</a> in 2011.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The final version of the opera, directed by the composer, was first performed on 8 August 2012 at the <a href=\"/wiki/Camden_Arts_Centre\" title=\"Camden Arts Centre\">Camden Arts Centre</a>, London, with subsequent performances at the <a href=\"/wiki/Courtauld_Gallery\" title=\"Courtauld Gallery\">Courtauld Gallery</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/T%C3%AAte_%C3%A0_T%C3%AAte_(opera_company)\" title=\"T\u00eate \u00e0 T\u00eate (opera company)\">T\u00eate \u00e0 T\u00eate Opera Festival</a>, the <a href=\"/wiki/Edinburgh_Fringe\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Edinburgh Fringe\">Edinburgh Fringe</a>, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_James_Joyce_Centre&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"The James Joyce Centre (page does not exist)\">The James Joyce Centre</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/National_Portrait_Gallery,_London\" title=\"National Portrait Gallery, London\">The National Portrait Gallery</a> and The <a href=\"/wiki/Hugh_Lane_Gallery\" title=\"Hugh Lane Gallery\">Hugh Lane Gallery</a>, which houses Bacon's studio, having been relocated from London to Dublin in 2001.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Picard_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Picard-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Scotsman_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Scotsman-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Roles_and_premiere_cast\">Roles and premiere cast</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Francis_Bacon_Opera&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Roles and premiere cast\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Francis Bacon (<a href=\"/wiki/Tenor\" title=\"Tenor\">tenor</a>) \u2013 created by <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Christopher_Killerby&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Christopher Killerby (page does not exist)\">Christopher Killerby</a></li>\n<li>Melvyn Bragg (tenor)  \u2013 created by <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Oliver_Brignall&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Oliver Brignall (page does not exist)\">Oliver Brignall</a></li></ul>\n<p>The pianist for the premiere performance was Genevieve Ellis.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Picard_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Picard-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Critical_reception\">Critical reception</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Francis_Bacon_Opera&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Critical reception\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Performances have polarised critics. Anna Picard in <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Independent\" title=\"The Independent\">The Independent</a></i> praised the work as having \"the rare quality of making people laugh with the music as much as the words\",<sup id=\"cite_ref-Picard_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Picard-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> while Malcolm Jack in <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Scotsman\" title=\"The Scotsman\">The Scotsman</a></i> derided it as \"silly, pretentious nonsense masquerading as experimental theatre.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Scotsman_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Scotsman-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Francis_Bacon_Opera&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Bragg, Melvyn (2010). <i>The South Bank Show: Final Cut</i>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=rNdaRKqOU18C&amp;pg=PT266&amp;lpg=PT266&amp;dq=francis+bacon+south+bank+show+1985&amp;source=bl&amp;ots=nEAlOnOOAa&amp;sig=XS6K1Tdsba8-Pnlxq66cCnOjTu8&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ei=-KcwUZywI-Wa0QXy2oDoCQ&amp;redir_esc=y\">Chapter 8: \"Francis Bacon (1985)\"</a>. Hachette UK</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">McDonnell, Keith (15 August 2011), <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.whatsonstage.com/news/theatre/opera/E8831313395243/Grimeborn+returns+to+the+Arcola+Theatre+.html\">\"Grimeborn returns to the Arcola Theatre\"</a>.<a href=\"/wiki/Whatsonstage.com\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Whatsonstage.com\">whatsonstage.com</a>.  Retrieved 1 March 2013,</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Picard-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Picard_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Picard_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Picard_3-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Picard, Anna (12 August 2012). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/classical/reviews/lheure-espagnole-lenfant-et-les-sortilges-glyndebourne-east-sussextte--tte-opera-festival-riverside-studios-londonthe-francis-bacon-opera-camden-arts-centre-london-8034577.html\">\"The Francis Bacon Opera, Camden Arts Centre, London\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Independent\" title=\"The Independent\">The Independent</a></i>. Retrieved 1 March 2013.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Scotsman-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Scotsman_4-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Scotsman_4-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Jack, Malcolm (23 August 2012). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.scotsman.com/the-scotsman/scotland/review-the-francis-bacon-opera-c-too-venue-4-1-2485246\">\"Review: The Francis Bacon Opera, C too (Venue 4)\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Scotsman\" title=\"The Scotsman\">The Scotsman</a></i>. Retrieved 1 March 2013.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Tanner, Michael (25 August 2012). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2741595171.html\">\"Opera Four play\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Spectator\" title=\"The Spectator\">The Spectator</a></i>. Retrieved 1 March 2013 via <a href=\"/wiki/Highbeam_Research\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Highbeam Research\">Highbeam Research</a> <span style=\"font-size:0.95em; font-size:90%; color:#555\">(subscription required)</span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Francis_Bacon_Opera&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Stevenson, Martin (17 August 2012). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.whatsonstage.com/news/theatre/london/E8831345409088/The+Francis+Bacon+Opera.html\">\"Review: <i>The Francis Bacon Opera</i></a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Whatsonstage.com\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Whatsonstage.com\">whatsonstage.com</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.tete-a-tete.org.uk/the-francis-bacon-opera/\"><i>The Francis Bacon Opera</i></a> at the T\u00eate \u00e0 T\u00eate Opera Festival</li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1234\nCached time: 20180831032637\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.060 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.074 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 192/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 702/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 108/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\n